urlText: Opal can be used between Wollongong and Moss Vale, Exeter and Bundanoon stations.
content:
If travelling by Coach between Wollongong station and Moss Vale, Exeter or Bundanoon stations you can use your Opal card or contactless card or device to tap on or off at your origin/destination station provided the origin/destination is an Opal enabled station.

If travelling onto Goulburn, or other Opal enabled station along the Southern Highlands Line, you should not tap off when transferring from Coach to an Intercity train but instead tap off at your destination station.

Booking is not required for Opal customers on this route.
subtitle: Opal can be used between Wollongong and Moss Vale, Exeter and Bundanoon stations.

urlText: Opal can be used between Bathurst and Lithgow Stations when booked
content: If travelling by Coach to or from Bathurst you can use your Opal card or contactless card or device to tap on or off at Bathurst station and your origin/destination station provided the origin/destination is an Opal enabled station. When using Opal you will need to reserve a seat, at no cost, through the Contact Centre by calling 13 22 32 (Between 07:00 to 22:00 each day).
subtitle: Opal can be used between Bathurst and Lithgow Stations when booked

urlText: Bondi Junction Interchange temporary bus stop changes
content:
Due to construction work at Bondi Junction interchange, there will be temporary bus stop changes from Tuesday 6 April to Monday 19 April 2021.

From 2am Tuesday 6 April to 2am Saturday 10 April and from 2am Monday 12 April to 2am Saturday 17 April:
  • Bus stop Bondi Junction Station, Stand A (Stop ID 202269) will close. The 333 routes towards North Bondi will use bus stop Bondi Junction Station Stand B (Stop ID202249).
  • Please note Bondi Junction Station, Stand A (Stop ID 202269) will be open for the 333 services on weekends.
From 2am Tuesday 6 April to 2am Monday 19 April:
  • Bus route 389 towards Bondi Junction Station will not stop at Bondi Junction Station, Grafton St, Stand G (Stop ID 202267). All customers will be dropped off at Bondi Junction Station, Grafton St, Stand S (Stop ID 202212).
  • The 389 bus route towards Pyrmont will not use bus stop Bondi Junction Station, Grafton St, Stand R (Stop ID 202281). The alternative stop will be Bondi Junction Station, Grafton St, Stand T (Stop ID 202213).
subtitle: Bondi Junction Interchange temporary bus stop changes

urlText: Phillip St, temporary bus stop closure
content:
From 20:00 Thursday 1 April to 05:00 Monday 19 April 2021, Parramatta Light Rail work will take place at the intersection of Phillip and Church Streets.

The bus stop Phillip St after Church St (TSN 2150377) will be closed and temporarily relocated on George St after Church St.

The 900 Parramatta Free Shuttle will be affected.

urlText: Brooklyn Ferry
content:
The Brooklyn ferry is only running during daylight hours due to flood debris in the water. 

On weekdays: 

The first service will be the 6:55am service from Little Wobby Wharf and the last service will be the 5:45pm service from Brooklyn. 

On the weekend: 

There will be no 7pm service from Brooklyn.
